25|$|Ethiopian {{agriculture}} is predominantly rain-fed subsistence agriculture, troubled by recurrent droughts. After Meles {{came to power}} in 1991, there were three major <b>droughts</b> <b>in</b> 1999/2000, 2002/2003 and 2009/2010.|$|R
